description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM UNTIL MARCH 2021 DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dedicated and enthusiastic clerical assistant to join the Flying Start Health Visiting Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work within Caerphilly borough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours of work are 18.75 hours per week and these will be worked Monday - Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be able to demonstrate excellent organisational and administrative skills with an eye for detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will require the successful candidate to have the ability to work under pressure and be able to demonstrate a commitment to achieving high quality standards of work and be flexible to the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are paramount to this post as you will be required to liaise with all levels of staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sian Paul - Business &amp; Administrative Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sian.paul@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07792 300403&lt;/p&gt;
